[Comentario en Core/Business Layer/DataAccess/ServerComponents/DbUtcClockCache.cs:106 por @Copilot]: When evicting a stale cache entry, the corresponding failure-throttle entry in s_LastCalibrationFailureUtcTicks is left behind indefinitely. In long-running processes with many distinct data sources that fail at least once, this dictionary can grow without bound even though the main cache entries are being evicted.
[Comentario en Core/Business Layer/DataAccess/ServerComponents/CachedDataProvider.cs:18 por @Copilot]: This newly introduced const name does not follow the file’s existing constant naming convention (e.g., STORED_PROC, SUBAREA) and the project guideline that const identifiers use UPPER_SNAKE_CASE. Renaming it will require updating all references to keep the file compiling.
[Comentario en Core/Business Layer/DataAccess/ServerComponents/DbUtcClockCache.cs:106 por @jimblythe-trimble]: Cached entries keyed by the connection DataSource (server name) are expected to be minimal and controlled by DevOps to not include frequent failure conditions. Failure handling and cache eviction primarily included for edge case validation through unit tests.

